LeagueInvaders2

by: Ryan Oh

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I made this game because I thought the previous League Invaders was too easy for the user, since the aliens weren't doing anything and there wasn't any special skills or attacks. Therefore, I added so that the aliens can directly shoot to the user, making it way harder.

2. What I Learned

I learned that my program was harder than I thought through testing it. My teacher gave me feedback to make more special skills, such as bombs, size change, and speed change of rocket.

3. Architecture of My Game

There are several classes all for different uses. There is a powerup class that deals with the size. If the rocket touches the soda can, it gets larger than the previous class. The bomb class is for when user touches the bomb, it automatically kills the aliens nearby. The speed class is when user touches the sword, it gets faster and smaller, giving a great advantage to the user.

4. Technical Implementation

I am proud of implementing images into the JFrame, making it more complex and complicated. I am proud of my program for implementing technologies that involve the alien to follow the direction of the user, constantly shooting bullets towards them .

5. Most Challenging Part

The most challenging part was the complexity of the program. The program itself contained so many classes, making it harder to debug the code when the program crashed. To find a single error, I had to look for it from every class. One letter could change the entire program. I overcame it by using print statements to find the source of error whenever the program crashed.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I would like to improve so that the rocket moves more smoothly with acceleration. If I continued to work on this program, I would implement more special skills to the user, such as a disaster that instantly kills everything (not only the aliens, but also special items).
